io.pivotal.rti.protocols

Interface ProtocolAdapter

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractProtocolAdapter

    public interface ProtocolAdapter
    Protocol Adapter API contract in protocols SDK. This is the primary entry point for contributing any new protocol adapter into an RTI deployment. However, it is not recommended to provide a direct implementation class but rather use a default implementation we provide and then override the abstract methods in it. Please see note below. There is a default abstract implementation for this interface provided at AbstractProtocolAdapter. It is highly recommended that the implementer of this interface extends the custom adapter from this abstract base class implementation and only overrides methods that do not have an implementation provided.

    • Method Detail

      • protocol

        java.lang.String protocol()
        Provides a humanized textual protocol name for this adapter. Implementations have to be careful to give a humanized name for the protocols as this is what the protocol adapter discovery system uses as a prefix to identify property keys. In addition, this value must match with any overridden property files that this adapter uses in it's classpath root. For example, if one implements protocol Foo, and the return value of this method happens to be foo, then the corresponding properties file must be named foo.properties at the root of the classpath with any overridden properties.
